    "In an experimental setting, such filters could be realized through arrays of resonators or waveguides tuned to specific frequency bands.Together, these principles establish a practical framework for developing acoustic neural networks that combine physical feasibility with competitive performance through constrained connectivity, hierarchical temporal integration, and interpretable frequency-selective filtering.",
